From 00ee23257898f1021c1d0f6996b188899caeaae9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Karthik M <karm@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Tue, 6 May 2025 12:00:45 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] Upstream: Protocol: Fix 2GHz Auto Channel Selection (ACS)
 issue

When 2GHz radio is configured with auto channel configuration,
Auto Channel Selection (ACS) algorithm will always pick
channel number 1 (2412MHz).

ACS algorithm tries to fetch first and last channel which
is not available for 2GHz. Hence it return NULL to the
acs_find_ideal_chan_mode() function. As a result, ACS fails
to find the channel and fallsback to the default
channel 1 (2412MHz).

Add support to fetch the start frequency for 2GHz when
bandwidth is configured as 20MHz.

Fixes: 1b0929883fb ("hostapd: OpenWrt patches update for
package upgrade 13.0")

Patch-work: None
Patch-dependency: p00-003-hostapd-add-acs_exclude_6ghz_non_psc-option-for-acs-.patch

Signed-off-by: Karthik M <karm@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 src/ap/acs.c | 16 ++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 16 insertions(+)

--- a/src/ap/acs.c
+++ b/src/ap/acs.c
@@ -476,6 +476,15 @@ static int *acs_get_bw_start_chan(u32 bw
 	*result_size = 0;
 
 	switch (bw) {
+	case 20:
+		freq_start_list = os_calloc(1 , sizeof(int));
+		if (!freq_start_list) {
+			*result_size = 0;
+			return NULL;
+		}
+		freq_start_list[*result_size] = chan->freq;
+		++(*result_size);
+		return freq_start_list;
 	case 40:
 		bandwidth_type = ACS_BW40;
 		break;
